 be paid, except where the accidental injury results in the amputation of an arm at the shoulder joint, or so close to shoulder joint that an artificial arm cannot be used, or results in the disarticulation of an arm at the shoulder joint, in which case compensation for an additional 65 weeks (if the accidental injury occurs on or after the effective date of this amendatory Act of the 94th General Assembly but before February 1, 2006) or an additional 70 weeks (if the accidental injury occurs on or after February 1, 2006) shall be paid.</font></code></div></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><div align="justify"><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">11. Foot-</font></code><br><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">155 weeks if the accidental injury occurs on or </font></code></div></td></tr><tr><td><table align="center" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td width="1"><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></code><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></code></td><td><div align="justify"><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">after the effective date of this amendatory Act of the 94th General Assembly but before February 1, 2006. </font></code></div></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><div align="justify"><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">167 weeks if the accidental injury occurs on or </font></code></div></td></tr><tr><td><table align="center" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td width="1"><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></code><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></code></td><td>