				</font></code></div></td></tr></table></body></html><br><a style="visibility: hidden" href='/legislation/ilcs/documents/082003050K26.htm'></a><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"><html><head><title>820 ILCS 305/26.1</title></head><body><table align="center" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="500"><tr><td><div align="justify"><p></p><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">(820 ILCS 305/26.1)</font></code> <code><font size="2" face="Courier New">
					</font></code><br><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">Sec. 26.1. </font></code><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">Misclassification of employees as independent contractors. </font></code><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">The Department of Labor, the Department of Employment Security, the Department of Revenue, the Office of the State Comptroller, and the Illinois Workers' Compensation Commission shall cooperate under the Employee Classification Act by sharing information concerning any suspected misclassification by an employer or entity, as defined in the Employee Classification Act, of one or more employees as independent contractors.</font></code><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">
</font></code><br><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">(Source: P.A. 95-26, eff. 1-1-08.)</font></code></div></td></tr></table></body></html><br><a style="visibility: hidden" href='/legislation/ilcs/documents/082003050K26.1.htm'></a><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"><html><head><title>820 ILCS 305/27</title></head><body><table align="center" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="500"><tr><td><div align="justify"><code><font size="2" face="Courier New">
